---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About | Andrew Lukosevic">
  <article>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-neutral-100">About</h1>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-neutral-100">Who I Am</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I'm a Sr. Manager at SentinelOne leading threat hunting and detection engineering efforts.
        I build teams and systems that find adversaries before they achieve their objectives.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
        After a decade in cybersecurity, my focus has shifted from reactive incident response to
        proactive threat hunting—finding the attacks that automated systems miss.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-neutral-100">Background</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        I started in a SOC as an L1 analyst, learning the fundamentals of security operations
        from the ground up. From there I moved into SIEM engineering with ArcSight and Trustwave,
        then back to the analyst track as an L2.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Incident response became my specialty—first as an IR analyst, then as Lead Incident
        Responder. I transitioned into SOC management before finding my current focus in
        threat hunting.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
        Along the way I've worked at AT&T, LevelBlue, and now SentinelOne—each role sharpening
        my perspective on how to detect and disrupt adversaries at scale.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-neutral-100">Current Focus</h2>
      <ul class="text-neutral-400 space-y-3">
        <li><span class="text-neutral-100">Threat Hunting</span> — Hypothesis-driven hunting to uncover advanced threats</li>
        <li><span class="text-neutral-100">Detection Engineering</span> — Building detections that actually catch real adversaries</li>
        <li><span class="text-neutral-100">AI-Augmented Security</span> — Leveraging AI to amplify human analysts</li>
        <li><span class="text-neutral-100">Team Building</span> — Developing threat hunters and scaling MDR operations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-medium mb-4 text-neutral-100">Outside of Work</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
        I'm an endurance hunter and outdoor enthusiast. I run <a href="https://youtube.com/@EndurHunt" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">EndurHunt</a>,
        where I create content about hunting and the outdoors. There's something about tracking
        and pursuing game that parallels the work of tracking adversaries—patience, pattern
        recognition, and persistence.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>
